[normal]Written Evidence from the 
[normal]Department for Transport (WRT 012)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Questions[bold]&#xa0;[bold]How resilient are the 
[normal]UK
[normal]’s transport networks (including road, rail and air) to adverse winter weather?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]What lessons have been learned since the severe weather experienced in the winter of 2009-10?  What practical changes have been made to ensure the 
[normal]UK
[normal] is now better equipped to deal with severe weather?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How well prepared are the Government, local authoriti
[normal]es and transport providers for adverse winter weather?  What more should be done to ensure a co-ordinated response?
